
Overview of adv comfortably

The adv comfortably has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (5) comfortably -- (in mental comfort; without stress; "he works comfortably on three continents")
2. (2) comfortably -- (in physical comfort; "she could have been lying comfortably in bed getting the same relief")
3. well, comfortably -- (in financial comfort; "They live well"; "she has been able to live comfortably since her husband died")
